senses
  entry
    definition "a vague idea in which some confidence is placed"
    examples ("his impression of her was favorable" "what are your feelings about the crisis?" "it strengthened my belief in his sincerity" "I had a feeling that she was lying")
    id oewn-05925333-n
    partOfSpeech n
    synonyms (impression feeling belief opinion)
  entry
    definition "a general inclusive concept"
    id oewn-05844922-n
    partOfSpeech n
  entry
    definition "an odd or fanciful or capricious idea"
    examples ("the theatrical notion of disguise is associated with disaster in his stories" "he had a whimsy about flying to the moon" "whimsy can be humorous to someone with time to enjoy it")
    id oewn-05928143-n
    partOfSpeech n
    synonyms (whim whimsy whimsey)
  entry
    definition "(usually plural) small personal articles or clothing or sewing items"
    examples ("buttons and needles are notions")
    id oewn-03838339-n
    partOfSpeech n
